[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":777},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F16\u002Fjs-weird-world-10-scope-chain\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F16\u002Fjs-weird-world-10-scope-chain\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F16\u002Fjs-weird-world-10-scope-chain\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F16\u002Fjs-weird-world-10-scope-chain\u002F":753,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F16\u002Fjs-weird-world-10-scope-chain\u002F":762},"\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F20190516\u002F4036061119\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":736,"date":737,"description":738,"extension":739,"lang":740,"meta":741,"navigation":70,"path":742,"readingMinutes":743,"seo":744,"standalone":745,"stem":746,"tags":747,"tldr":750,"updated":737,"url":751,"__hash__":752},"content\u002Fen\u002FJsWeirdWorld\u002Fjs-weird-world-10-scope-chain.md","[JS Weird World] No.10 The Scope Chain","1000007922",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":732},"minimark",[11,16,20,142,157,164,175,181,210,219,225,232,246,260,265,271,276,288,368,383,396,476,479,485,495,502,507,522,598,602,605,611,614,679,685,691,697,702,716,720,728],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"the-scope-chain","The Scope Chain",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Next up is the scope chain. Honestly this one isn't too hard, because we've already practiced it a bunch in the earlier posts — and the last chapter actually already touched on the scope chain. Like always, let's learn it straight from the course example code.",[21,22,27],"pre",{"className":23,"code":24,"language":25,"meta":26,"style":26},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","function b() {\n console.log(myVar);\n}\n\nfunction a() {\n var myVar = 2;\n b();\n}\n\nvar myVar = 1;\na();\n","js","",[28,29,30,47,59,65,72,82,101,109,114,119,134],"code",{"__ignoreMap":26},[31,32,35,39,43],"span",{"class":33,"line":34},"line",1,[31,36,38],{"class":37},"sWyjQ","function",[31,40,42],{"class":41},"sj_SG"," b",[31,44,46],{"class":45},"sMAXC","() {\n",[31,48,50,53,56],{"class":33,"line":49},2,[31,51,52],{"class":45}," console.",[31,54,55],{"class":41},"log",[31,57,58],{"class":45},"(myVar);\n",[31,60,62],{"class":33,"line":61},3,[31,63,64],{"class":45},"}\n",[31,66,68],{"class":33,"line":67},4,[31,69,71],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":70},true,"\n",[31,73,75,77,80],{"class":33,"line":74},5,[31,76,38],{"class":37},[31,78,79],{"class":41}," a",[31,81,46],{"class":45},[31,83,85,88,91,94,98],{"class":33,"line":84},6,[31,86,87],{"class":37}," var",[31,89,90],{"class":45}," myVar ",[31,92,93],{"class":37},"=",[31,95,97],{"class":96},"sCcAr"," 2",[31,99,100],{"class":45},";\n",[31,102,104,106],{"class":33,"line":103},7,[31,105,42],{"class":41},[31,107,108],{"class":45},"();\n",[31,110,112],{"class":33,"line":111},8,[31,113,64],{"class":45},[31,115,117],{"class":33,"line":116},9,[31,118,71],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":70},[31,120,122,125,127,129,132],{"class":33,"line":121},10,[31,123,124],{"class":37},"var",[31,126,90],{"class":45},[31,128,93],{"class":37},[31,130,131],{"class":96}," 1",[31,133,100],{"class":45},[31,135,137,140],{"class":33,"line":136},11,[31,138,139],{"class":41},"a",[31,141,108],{"class":45},[17,143,144,145,148,149,152,153,156],{},"The thing to notice here is function ",[28,146,147],{},"b()"," — it never declares a variable (",[28,150,151],{},"var myVar","), it just ",[28,154,155],{},"console.log","s it directly.",[17,158,159],{},[160,161],"img",{"alt":162,"src":163},"b logging myVar","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FsmvaiMX.png",[17,165,166,167,170,171,174],{},"We find that ",[28,168,169],{},"myVar"," is actually ",[28,172,173],{},"1","?! Why is that? First, let's think about the execution stack while the functions run.",[17,176,177],{},[160,178],{"alt":179,"src":180},"execution stack","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FSdFWf6c.png",[17,182,183,184,187,188,190,191,195,196,199,200,202,203,206,207,209],{},"You can see that both function ",[28,185,186],{},"a()"," and function ",[28,189,147],{}," are stacked on top of the ",[192,193,194],"strong",{},"global environment object",". That means the ",[28,197,198],{},"var myVar = 1;"," created on the ",[192,201,194],{}," can be called and accessed by ",[192,204,205],{},"other execution contexts"," — unless you create a variable with the same name inside a function, in which case it won't reach for the global ",[28,208,198],{},".",[17,211,212,213,215,216,218],{},"Using the course's diagram, it looks like this — at run time, there's no ",[28,214,169],{}," inside ",[28,217,147],{},":",[17,220,221],{},[160,222],{"alt":223,"src":224},"no myVar inside b","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fd8hSViB.png",[17,226,227,228,231],{},"And JavaScript is kind of special: it doesn't only look for variables in the ",[192,229,230],{},"default execution context",". So note that every execution context creates two things:",[233,234,235,239],"ul",{},[236,237,238],"li",{},"a global environment object",[236,240,241,242,245],{},"the ",[192,243,244],{},"this"," variable",[17,247,248,249,252,253,255,256,259],{},"The course also mentioned that JavaScript refers to the ",[192,250,251],{},"outer environment",". So what's the outer environment? Take function ",[28,254,147],{}," — its outer environment is the ",[192,257,258],{},"global execution context",", just like in the course slide.",[17,261,262],{},[160,263],{"alt":258,"src":264},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FqUXTrVJ.png",[17,266,267,268,270],{},"And ",[28,269,186],{}," is the same.",[17,272,273],{},[160,274],{"alt":258,"src":275},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FpedcXBi.png",[17,277,278,279,282,283,285,286,209],{},"This chapter has one key point: how do we figure out ",[192,280,281],{},"which outer environment it refers to?"," This is where the \"lexical environment\" comes in. For function ",[28,284,147],{},", where is its lexical environment? Think about the environment in which we created function ",[28,287,147],{},[21,289,290],{"className":23,"code":24,"language":25,"meta":26,"style":26},[28,291,292,300,308,312,316,324,336,342,346,350,362],{"__ignoreMap":26},[31,293,294,296,298],{"class":33,"line":34},[31,295,38],{"class":37},[31,297,42],{"class":41},[31,299,46],{"class":45},[31,301,302,304,306],{"class":33,"line":49},[31,303,52],{"class":45},[31,305,55],{"class":41},[31,307,58],{"class":45},[31,309,310],{"class":33,"line":61},[31,311,64],{"class":45},[31,313,314],{"class":33,"line":67},[31,315,71],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":70},[31,317,318,320,322],{"class":33,"line":74},[31,319,38],{"class":37},[31,321,79],{"class":41},[31,323,46],{"class":45},[31,325,326,328,330,332,334],{"class":33,"line":84},[31,327,87],{"class":37},[31,329,90],{"class":45},[31,331,93],{"class":37},[31,333,97],{"class":96},[31,335,100],{"class":45},[31,337,338,340],{"class":33,"line":103},[31,339,42],{"class":41},[31,341,108],{"class":45},[31,343,344],{"class":33,"line":111},[31,345,64],{"class":45},[31,347,348],{"class":33,"line":116},[31,349,71],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":70},[31,351,352,354,356,358,360],{"class":33,"line":121},[31,353,124],{"class":37},[31,355,90],{"class":45},[31,357,93],{"class":37},[31,359,131],{"class":96},[31,361,100],{"class":45},[31,363,364,366],{"class":33,"line":136},[31,365,139],{"class":41},[31,367,108],{"class":45},[17,369,370,371,373,374,376,377,379,380,209],{},"From the code we can tell function ",[28,372,147],{}," is created in the global environment, not inside ",[28,375,186],{},". So ",[28,378,147],{},"'s ",[192,381,382],{},"outer environment is the global environment",[17,384,385,386,388,389,391,392,395],{},"Now what about this? Where's ",[28,387,147],{},"'s lexical environment? And what's ",[28,390,147],{},"'s outer environment now? What will ",[28,393,394],{},"console.log(myVar);"," be?",[21,397,399],{"className":23,"code":398,"language":25,"meta":26,"style":26},"function a() {\n var myVar = 2;\n b();\n function b() {\n  console.log(myVar);\n }\n}\n\nvar myVar = 1;\na();\n",[28,400,401,409,421,427,436,445,450,454,458,470],{"__ignoreMap":26},[31,402,403,405,407],{"class":33,"line":34},[31,404,38],{"class":37},[31,406,79],{"class":41},[31,408,46],{"class":45},[31,410,411,413,415,417,419],{"class":33,"line":49},[31,412,87],{"class":37},[31,414,90],{"class":45},[31,416,93],{"class":37},[31,418,97],{"class":96},[31,420,100],{"class":45},[31,422,423,425],{"class":33,"line":61},[31,424,42],{"class":41},[31,426,108],{"class":45},[31,428,429,432,434],{"class":33,"line":67},[31,430,431],{"class":37}," function",[31,433,42],{"class":41},[31,435,46],{"class":45},[31,437,438,441,443],{"class":33,"line":74},[31,439,440],{"class":45},"  console.",[31,442,55],{"class":41},[31,444,58],{"class":45},[31,446,447],{"class":33,"line":84},[31,448,449],{"class":45}," }\n",[31,451,452],{"class":33,"line":103},[31,453,64],{"class":45},[31,455,456],{"class":33,"line":111},[31,457,71],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":70},[31,459,460,462,464,466,468],{"class":33,"line":116},[31,461,124],{"class":37},[31,463,90],{"class":45},[31,465,93],{"class":37},[31,467,131],{"class":96},[31,469,100],{"class":45},[31,471,472,474],{"class":33,"line":121},[31,473,139],{"class":41},[31,475,108],{"class":45},[17,477,478],{},"As long as you've got the earlier concept down, you already know the answer.",[17,480,481],{},[160,482],{"alt":483,"src":484},"lexical environment","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FtM9dU45h.png",[17,486,487,488,491,492,209],{},"But here's another key point to watch: JavaScript is special — it really ",[192,489,490],{},"cares about the lexical environment",". So when a variable can't be found in a given execution context, it goes and ",[192,493,494],{},"looks for the variable in the outer environment instead",[17,496,497,498,501],{},"And this whole process is the ",[192,499,500],{},"scope chain"," (just like an actual chain).",[17,503,504],{},[160,505],{"alt":500,"src":506},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FZS8vMqTh.png",[17,508,509,510,512,513,515,516,518,519,521],{},"So when function ",[28,511,147],{}," can't find ",[28,514,169],{},", it goes down to the outer environment to look — and that behavior is what we call the ",[192,517,500],{},". It doesn't necessarily jump straight to the last outer environment; it depends on the ",[192,520,483],{},", just like the example I just wrote.",[21,523,524],{"className":23,"code":398,"language":25,"meta":26,"style":26},[28,525,526,534,546,552,560,568,572,576,580,592],{"__ignoreMap":26},[31,527,528,530,532],{"class":33,"line":34},[31,529,38],{"class":37},[31,531,79],{"class":41},[31,533,46],{"class":45},[31,535,536,538,540,542,544],{"class":33,"line":49},[31,537,87],{"class":37},[31,539,90],{"class":45},[31,541,93],{"class":37},[31,543,97],{"class":96},[31,545,100],{"class":45},[31,547,548,550],{"class":33,"line":61},[31,549,42],{"class":41},[31,551,108],{"class":45},[31,553,554,556,558],{"class":33,"line":67},[31,555,431],{"class":37},[31,557,42],{"class":41},[31,559,46],{"class":45},[31,561,562,564,566],{"class":33,"line":74},[31,563,440],{"class":45},[31,565,55],{"class":41},[31,567,58],{"class":45},[31,569,570],{"class":33,"line":84},[31,571,449],{"class":45},[31,573,574],{"class":33,"line":103},[31,575,64],{"class":45},[31,577,578],{"class":33,"line":111},[31,579,71],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":70},[31,581,582,584,586,588,590],{"class":33,"line":116},[31,583,124],{"class":37},[31,585,90],{"class":45},[31,587,93],{"class":37},[31,589,131],{"class":96},[31,591,100],{"class":45},[31,593,594,596],{"class":33,"line":121},[31,595,139],{"class":41},[31,597,108],{"class":45},[17,599,600],{},[160,601],{"alt":500,"src":484},[17,603,604],{},"At this point it works just like the course slide.",[17,606,607],{},[160,608],{"alt":609,"src":610},"slide","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F56hfnzth.png",[17,612,613],{},"Now what if I change it like this?",[21,615,617],{"className":23,"code":616,"language":25,"meta":26,"style":26},"function a() {\n b();\n functio